<article>
    <h1>Take more care when dis&#xAD;play&#xAD;ing national flag</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200815/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-15"><time>2020-08-15</time></a>
        - <span>FORUM</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Since our national flag does not have a sym­met­ri­cal de­sign like those of cer­tain coun­tries, like Ja­pan, Is­rael, Aus­tria or Thai­land, more care needs to be taken when dis­play­ing it.</p>
    <p>Re­cently, as I was ad­mir­ing the</p>
    <p>Sky Habi­tat and Sky Vue con­do­mini­ums, I very quickly spot­ted two flags flipped hor­i­zon­tally at the two con­do­mini­ums.</p>
    <p>It would be nice if friends, rel­a­tives or even the con­do­minium’s man­age­ment could gen­tly alert these peo­ple as soon as pos­si­ble if they spot such cases. This should be an ex­er­cise not to em­bar­rass peo­ple, but to in­form. Lim Poh Seng</p>


</article>

